<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FFA5FFEFA7ADFEE7FC28DE98" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0755A263FFA5FFEFA7ADFEE7FEF0DD23" blockId="60.[189,310,264,290]" box="[189,310,264,290]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<heading id="5C1D150FFFA5FFEFA7ADFEE7FEF0DD23" bold="true" box="[189,310,264,290]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFA5FFEFA7ADFEE7FEF0DD23" bold="true" box="[189,310,264,290]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FFA5FFEFA7ADFED7FC28DE98" blockId="60.[187,1401,312,665]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
Based on 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FFA5FFEFA620FED7FDB8DD52" author="Giupponi A. P. L. &amp; Miranda G. S." box="[304,638,312,339]" firstAuthor="Giupponi" journalOrPublisher="PLoS One" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="0148277" part="11" refId="ref148797" refString="Giupponi A. P. L. &amp; Miranda G. S. 2016. Eight new species of Charinus Simon, 1892 (Arachnida: Amblypygi: Charinidae) endemic for the Brazilian Amazon, with notes on their conservational status. PLoS One 11: e 0148277. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0148277" title="Eight new species of Charinus Simon, 1892 (Arachnida: Amblypygi: Charinidae) endemic for the Brazilian Amazon, with notes on their conservational status" type="journal article" year="2016">
Giupponi &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="C52E6C81FFA5FFEFA6D4FED7FDE1DD53" box="[452,551,312,338]" country="Venezuela" name="Miranda" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Miranda</collectingRegion>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, this species may be separated from other 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFA5FFEFA37DFED7FB1CDD53" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[1133,1242,312,338]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFA5FFEFA37DFED7FB1CDD53" box="[1133,1242,312,338]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Charinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Amazonia and northern South America by means of the following combination of characters: tegument pale yellow; cushion-like female gonopod with lateral projections directed posteriorly, covering opening of internal seminal receptacles (atrium); median and lateral eyes present, but median ocular tubercle and lateral eyes markedly reduced, as in 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFA5FFEFA50AFE26FD52DDE2" authorityName="Giupponi &amp; Miranda" authorityYear="2016" box="[538,660,457,483]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carajas">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFA5FFEFA50AFE26FD52DDE2" box="[538,660,457,483]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">C. carajas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; median ocular tubercle situated in depression; small, rounded tetra- and pentasternum; weakly sclerotized margin of sternum; pedipalp femur with three dorsal spines; proximal spine of pedipalp tarsus ca one-quarter length of distal spine; tibia of leg I with 21 articles, tarsus I with 37 articles; leg IV basitibia with three pseudo-articles; leg IV basitibia trichobothrium 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFA5FFEFA7ADFDB4FF12DE74" box="[189,212,603,629]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">bt</emphasis>
situated in proximal third; leg IV distitibia with 16 trichobothria; leg IV distitibia 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFA5FFEFA3DFFDB4FB20DE74" box="[1231,1254,603,629]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">bf</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFA5FFEFA3E8FDB4FAD2DE74" box="[1272,1300,603,629]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">bc</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFA5FFEFA244FDB4FAB0DE74" box="[1364,1398,603,629]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">sbf</emphasis>
trichobothria equidistant; 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFA5FFEFA6FCFD6FFDC2DE98" box="[492,516,640,665]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">sc</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFA5FFEFA52DFD90FD97DE98" box="[573,593,639,665]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">sf</emphasis>
series each with five trichobothria.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FFA5FFEFA7ADFD2EFDD4DF31" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="0755A263FFA5FFEFA7ADFD2EFE82DEDA" blockId="60.[189,324,705,731]" box="[189,324,705,731]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<heading id="5C1D150FFFA5FFEFA7ADFD2EFE82DEDA" bold="true" box="[189,324,705,731]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFA5FFEFA7ADFD2EFE82DEDA" bold="true" box="[189,324,705,731]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FFA5FFEFA7ADFD1EFDD4DF31" blockId="60.[189,1399,753,816]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
Latin adjective meaning ‘eastern’, referring to the Sierra Leste mountain range inhabited by the species (
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FFA5FFEFA7D5FCFAFDC0DF31" author="Giupponi A. P. L. &amp; Miranda G. S." box="[197,518,789,816]" firstAuthor="Giupponi" journalOrPublisher="PLoS One" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="0148277" part="11" refId="ref148797" refString="Giupponi A. P. L. &amp; Miranda G. S. 2016. Eight new species of Charinus Simon, 1892 (Arachnida: Amblypygi: Charinidae) endemic for the Brazilian Amazon, with notes on their conservational status. PLoS One 11: e 0148277. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0148277" title="Eight new species of Charinus Simon, 1892 (Arachnida: Amblypygi: Charinidae) endemic for the Brazilian Amazon, with notes on their conservational status" type="journal article" year="2016">
Giupponi &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="C52E6C81FFA5FFEFA64BFCFAFE78DF2E" box="[347,446,789,815]" country="Venezuela" name="Miranda" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Miranda</collectingRegion>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
